[
    {
        "text": "Are you using the expression 'me too' too \noften in your daily conversations?",
        "start": 0.123,
        "duration": 5.227
    },
    {
        "text": " Sometimes, that's actually the wrong expression.",
        "start": 5.511,
        "duration": 3.196
    },
    {
        "text": "And, sometimes you can find a better alternative.",
        "start": 8.707,
        "duration": 3.749
    },
    {
        "text": "Make sure you watch the lesson till the end, \nwhere you will discover an amusing common mistake.",
        "start": 12.647,
        "duration": 5.629
    },
    {
        "text": "A quick reminder that there are lots of free \nexercises on my online course for you to enjoy.",
        "start": 18.8,
        "duration": 6.16
    },
    {
        "text": "You can access these by creating a free \naccount on my website,",
        "start": 24.96,
        "duration": 4.602
    },
    {
        "text": "Anglo-Link.com.",
        "start": 29.562,
        "duration": 1.579
    },
    {
        "text": "The link to set up your free \naccount is in the description box.",
        "start": 31.52,
        "duration": 4.204
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay! Let's start by looking at an example of \nwhen we say 'me too'.",
        "start": 36.08,
        "duration": 5.413
    },
    {
        "text": "So, someone has said to you:",
        "start": 42.542,
        "duration": 1.825
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm interested in antique furniture.",
        "start": 44.367,
        "duration": 2.422
    },
    {
        "text": "And, you're also interested in antique furniture.",
        "start": 46.789,
        "duration": 2.491
    },
    {
        "text": "You can simply say:",
        "start": 49.28,
        "duration": 1.451
    },
    {
        "text": "Me too.",
        "start": 50.731,
        "duration": 0.922
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, you may very occasionally hear:",
        "start": 52.149,
        "duration": 2.758
    },
    {
        "text": "I too.",
        "start": 54.907,
        "duration": 0.921
    },
    {
        "text": "That's very formal.",
        "start": 55.828,
        "duration": 1.212
    },
    {
        "text": "It's grammatically correct. But, it's very formal. \nI would avoid that.",
        "start": 57.04,
        "duration": 3.937
    },
    {
        "text": "Just stick with 'me too'.",
        "start": 60.977,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let's look at some alternatives.",
        "start": 63.731,
        "duration": 2.165
    },
    {
        "text": "One good one is:",
        "start": 66.653,
        "duration": 1.315
    },
    {
        "text": "Same here.",
        "start": 67.968,
        "duration": 0.879
    },
    {
        "text": "It's simple, and it works every time.",
        "start": 68.847,
        "duration": 2.527
    },
    {
        "text": "But, two things that you must absolutely avoid \nis using 'also' and 'as well' in this expression.",
        "start": 72.0,
        "duration": 7.12
    },
    {
        "text": "Although, they're synonyms for 'too', they don't \nfit here.",
        "start": 79.593,
        "duration": 4.504
    },
    {
        "text": "So, don't say:",
        "start": 84.097,
        "duration": 1.272
    },
    {
        "text": "Me also",
        "start": 85.369,
        "duration": 0.854
    },
    {
        "text": "And don't say:",
        "start": 86.223,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "Me as well",
        "start": 87.393,
        "duration": 0.987
    },
    {
        "text": "Right! Let's look at two more alternatives.",
        "start": 88.584,
        "duration": 2.604
    },
    {
        "text": "These are short sentences that you create using the verb in the original sentence.",
        "start": 91.188,
        "duration": 6.997
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, here the verb is 'am'. So, we use that:",
        "start": 98.185,
        "duration": 3.815
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm interested in antique furniture.",
        "start": 102.0,
        "duration": 2.478
    },
    {
        "text": "I am too.",
        "start": 104.478,
        "duration": 0.966
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 105.72,
        "duration": 0.645
    },
    {
        "text": "So am I.",
        "start": 106.365,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, notice that if you start with 'so', we need a subject verb inversion.",
        "start": 108.236,
        "duration": 5.464
    },
    {
        "text": "We have to swap 'am' and 'I':",
        "start": 113.7,
        "duration": 3.07
    },
    {
        "text": "So am I.",
        "start": 116.77,
        "duration": 1.63
    },
    {
        "text": "Now! A common mistake that I hear some of my \nstudents make,",
        "start": 118.4,
        "duration": 4.112
    },
    {
        "text": "is sticking with the verb 'am'.",
        "start": 122.512,
        "duration": 3.223
    },
    {
        "text": "no matter what the original sentence is, they say:",
        "start": 125.735,
        "duration": 3.909
    },
    {
        "text": "Oh! I am too.",
        "start": 129.644,
        "duration": 1.159
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 130.803,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "So am I.",
        "start": 131.303,
        "duration": 0.752
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, be careful because this has to follow the original sentence.",
        "start": 132.055,
        "duration": 5.318
    },
    {
        "text": "So, for example, if someone says:",
        "start": 137.373,
        "duration": 1.767
    },
    {
        "text": "I like antique furniture.",
        "start": 139.14,
        "duration": 2.114
    },
    {
        "text": "We're using the Present Simple tense.",
        "start": 141.254,
        "duration": 2.428
    },
    {
        "text": "We need to use the auxiliary of the Present Simple tense.",
        "start": 143.682,
        "duration": 3.545
    },
    {
        "text": "So, don't say:",
        "start": 147.227,
        "duration": 1.29
    },
    {
        "text": "I am to.",
        "start": 148.517,
        "duration": 1.199
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to say:",
        "start": 149.716,
        "duration": 1.154
    },
    {
        "text": "I do too.",
        "start": 150.87,
        "duration": 1.519
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 152.389,
        "duration": 0.688
    },
    {
        "text": "So do I.",
        "start": 153.077,
        "duration": 1.528
    },
    {
        "text": "And! If we change the tense, obviously we need to change the auxiliary.",
        "start": 154.853,
        "duration": 4.619
    },
    {
        "text": " So, if someone said:",
        "start": 159.472,
        "duration": 1.971
    },
    {
        "text": "I used to like antique furniture.",
        "start": 161.443,
        "duration": 2.477
    },
    {
        "text": "You need to say:",
        "start": 163.92,
        "duration": 1.436
    },
    {
        "text": "I did too.",
        "start": 165.356,
        "duration": 1.521
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 166.877,
        "duration": 0.689
    },
    {
        "text": "So did I.",
        "start": 167.566,
        "duration": 1.053
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, what about negative statements?",
        "start": 168.619,
        "duration": 2.612
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, someone says:",
        "start": 171.231,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't like antique furniture.",
        "start": 173.471,
        "duration": 2.265
    },
    {
        "text": "What you must avoid here is using 'too'.",
        "start": 176.29,
        "duration": 3.513
    },
    {
        "text": "'Too' doesn't work with a negative sentence.",
        "start": 179.803,
        "duration": 3.06
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to switch to 'neither'.",
        "start": 182.863,
        "duration": 2.708
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't like antique furniture.",
        "start": 185.745,
        "duration": 2.414
    },
    {
        "text": " Me neither.",
        "start": 188.159,
        "duration": 1.666
    },
    {
        "text": "Interestingly, and happily, 'same here' works here too.",
        "start": 189.825,
        "duration": 5.059
    },
    {
        "text": " 'Same here' is very versatile.",
        "start": 194.884,
        "duration": 2.156
    },
    {
        "text": "It works with positive sentences and negative sentences.",
        "start": 197.04,
        "duration": 4.127
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's look at the other alternatives.",
        "start": 201.968,
        "duration": 2.117
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't like antique furniture.",
        "start": 204.48,
        "duration": 2.573
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't.",
        "start": 207.403,
        "duration": 0.805
    },
    {
        "text": "You can't use too.",
        "start": 208.936,
        "duration": 1.534
    },
    {
        "text": "The word you need to use here is 'either'.",
        "start": 210.47,
        "duration": 3.064
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't either.",
        "start": 213.534,
        "duration": 2.179
    },
    {
        "text": "And, if you want to use the inversion, then use 'neither'.",
        "start": 215.917,
        "duration": 4.813
    },
    {
        "text": "Neither do I.",
        "start": 220.992,
        "duration": 1.883
    },
    {
        "text": "And, if we change the tense, obviously, the same thing:",
        "start": 223.44,
        "duration": 3.682
    },
    {
        "text": "I didn't used to like antique furniture.",
        "start": 227.122,
        "duration": 2.714
    },
    {
        "text": " I didn't either.",
        "start": 229.836,
        "duration": 1.693
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 231.529,
        "duration": 0.878
    },
    {
        "text": "Neither did I.",
        "start": 232.407,
        "duration": 1.359
    },
    {
        "text": "Now! a little word about negative words.",
        "start": 234.422,
        "duration": 2.954
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, 'never', 'hardly', 'no longer'. Let's look at some examples:",
        "start": 237.376,
        "duration": 5.344
    },
    {
        "text": "I've never bought any antique furniture.",
        "start": 242.72,
        "duration": 2.94
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, you see that the verb is positive: 'I have'.",
        "start": 245.66,
        "duration": 3.254
    },
    {
        "text": "But, the sentence, the idea is negative because of 'never'.",
        "start": 248.914,
        "duration": 4.004
    },
    {
        "text": "Make sure you follow with the negative expression.",
        "start": 252.918,
        "duration": 3.083
    },
    {
        "text": "So, don't use 'too' or 'so'.",
        "start": 256.001,
        "duration": 2.426
    },
    {
        "text": "Say:",
        "start": 258.427,
        "duration": 0.922
    },
    {
        "text": "Me neither.",
        "start": 259.349,
        "duration": 0.733
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 260.082,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "I haven't either.",
        "start": 260.902,
        "duration": 1.548
    },
    {
        "text": "Or:",
        "start": 262.45,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Neither have I.",
        "start": 262.95,
        "duration": 1.69
    },
    {
        "text": "Let's look at an example with 'hardly'.",
        "start": 264.64,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": " I can hardly see the road.",
        "start": 267.22,
        "duration": 2.131
    },
    {
        "text": "Me neither.",
        "start": 269.846,
        "duration": 1.797
    },
    {
        "text": "I can't either.",
        "start": 271.643,
        "duration": 1.577
    },
    {
        "text": "Neither can I.",
        "start": 273.84,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "And, a final example with 'no longer'.",
        "start": 275.568,
        "duration": 2.97
    },
    {
        "text": "John no longer works here.",
        "start": 278.975,
        "duration": 2.262
    },
    {
        "text": "Linda neither.",
        "start": 281.528,
        "duration": 2.124
    },
    {
        "text": "Linda doesn't either.",
        "start": 284.264,
        "duration": 2.078
    },
    {
        "text": "Neither does Linda.",
        "start": 286.619,
        "duration": 1.923
    },
    {
        "text": "And, there is one other word I want to mention here, and that's the word 'nor.",
        "start": 289.183,
        "duration": 5.002
    },
    {
        "text": "'Nor' can replace 'neither' in an inverted phrase.",
        "start": 294.185,
        "duration": 4.244
    },
    {
        "text": "But, it sounds a little bit more formal.",
        "start": 298.429,
        "duration": 2.277
    },
    {
        "text": " So, you may hear and if you're in a formal situation, you can say:",
        "start": 300.706,
        "duration": 4.094
    },
    {
        "text": "Nor did I.",
        "start": 305.36,
        "duration": 1.121
    },
    {
        "text": "Nor does she.",
        "start": 306.904,
        "duration": 1.412
    },
    {
        "text": "Nor would they.",
        "start": 308.709,
        "duration": 1.185
    },
    {
        "text": "Now! I'd like to share an amusing common mistake with you.",
        "start": 310.331,
        "duration": 4.419
    },
    {
        "text": "If someone says to you:",
        "start": 315.28,
        "duration": 1.437
    },
    {
        "text": "I love you!",
        "start": 316.717,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": "I've often heard the other person by mistake saying:",
        "start": 317.727,
        "duration": 3.705
    },
    {
        "text": "Me too.",
        "start": 321.432,
        "duration": 0.968
    },
    {
        "text": "I do too.",
        "start": 322.4,
        "duration": 1.08
    },
    {
        "text": "So do I.",
        "start": 323.48,
        "duration": 1.093
    },
    {
        "text": "Obviously, this means I love myself too.",
        "start": 324.927,
        "duration": 3.69
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't think that's what you want to say.",
        "start": 328.617,
        "duration": 2.279
    },
    {
        "text": "In this situation, avoid these expressions!",
        "start": 330.896,
        "duration": 3.376
    },
    {
        "text": "You have to repeat the sentence. You have to say:",
        "start": 334.272,
        "duration": 2.608
    },
    {
        "text": "I love you too.",
        "start": 336.88,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, there are a couple of other situations that you need to be careful of.",
        "start": 338.8,
        "duration": 4.298
    },
    {
        "text": "Same type of situation. If someone says:",
        "start": 343.098,
        "duration": 3.595
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm happy to see you.",
        "start": 346.693,
        "duration": 1.447
    },
    {
        "text": "Don't say: Me too.",
        "start": 348.14,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "Because it means I'm happy to see myself, right? That \ndoesn't work.",
        "start": 349.68,
        "duration": 4.114
    },
    {
        "text": "You either have to repeat the sentence.",
        "start": 353.794,
        "duration": 2.098
    },
    {
        "text": "Maybe you can change the vocabulary \na little bit. Say:",
        "start": 355.892,
        "duration": 3.83
    },
    {
        "text": "It's good to see you too.",
        "start": 359.722,
        "duration": 1.798
    },
    {
        "text": "Or use this very useful expression:",
        "start": 361.52,
        "duration": 3.177
    },
    {
        "text": "Likewise.",
        "start": 364.697,
        "duration": 1.258
    },
    {
        "text": "That reciprocates whatever nice thing they have said to you.",
        "start": 365.955,
        "duration": 4.826
    },
    {
        "text": "And the last example.",
        "start": 370.781,
        "duration": 2.195
    },
    {
        "text": "Someone wishes you a lovely day:",
        "start": 372.976,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Have a lovely day.",
        "start": 374.976,
        "duration": 1.264
    },
    {
        "text": "Here, simply say:",
        "start": 376.24,
        "duration": 1.85
    },
    {
        "text": "You too!",
        "start": 378.09,
        "duration": 0.923
    },
    {
        "text": "You are sending the same wish back to them in this way.",
        "start": 379.013,
        "duration": 4.797
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, that's the end of my conversation tips for today.",
        "start": 384.559,
        "duration": 3.602
    },
    {
        "text": "You'll find more conversation tips in this playlist.",
        "start": 388.161,
        "duration": 3.924
    },
    {
        "text": "Also, make sure you check out my online course \nfor lots of exercises on all the topics that I teach.",
        "start": 392.56,
        "duration": 6.416
    },
    {
        "text": "And, please remember to like, subscribe, \nand allow notifications as well.",
        "start": 398.976,
        "duration": 5.264
    },
    {
        "text": "Thanks a lot for watching. I look forward to seeing you \nin my next lesson very soon.",
        "start": 404.24,
        "duration": 5.255
    },
    {
        "text": "Goodbye for now.",
        "start": 409.495,
        "duration": 1.302
    }
]